The **individual coaching** offered by All Leaders Initiative is structured support of 8 to 12 sessions of 1.5 hours with a certified professional coach, open to any employee at any hierarchical level. It provides a confidential and safe space to develop skills, performance, self-confidence and motivation — serving both the individual and the organization.

### The approach is structured in four stages
1. an **exploratory meeting** allowing the coachee to meet up to three coaches and freely choose theirs;
2. a **tripartite meeting** with an organization representative to co-construct objectives;
3. the **coaching sessions** themselves, focused on the coachee's solutions rather than external prescriptions;
4. finally a **final tripartite review** to measure progress and share learning.

### Topics covered
Topics covered include self-awareness, stress and conflict management, managerial positioning, ability to bring people together and emotional intelligence. Documented results are solid: according to the International Coaching Federation, 80% of coachees report improved confidence and stress management, and ROI can reach 5 to 7 times the initial cost.

